                        }, 
                        {
                            "source": "Bestiary 3", 
                            "sections": [], 
                            "type": "section", 
                            "text": "<ul class=\"stat-block-2\"><li>Magical effects that heal living creatures slow a bone golem (as the <i>slow</i> spell) for 1d4 rounds (no save).</li>\n<li>A magical attack that deals negative energy damage breaks any <i>slow</i> effect on the golem and heals 1 point of damage for every 3 points of damage the attack would otherwise deal. If the healing would cause the golem to exceed its full normal hit points, it gains any excess as temporary hit points. A bone golem gets no saving throw against attacks that deal negative energy damage.</li>\n<li>A <i>raise dead</i>, <i>resurrection</i>, or <i>true resurrection</i> spell negates its DR and immunity to magic for 1 minute.</li></ul>"
                        }, 
